locations.title: Arishna Chandra
locations.description: Arishna is a warm and empathic Psychologist with over 10 years experience treating a broad range of issues and clinical presentations including, anxiety, depression, PTSD, complex trauma, grief and loss, transition and adjustment issues, self-esteem and confidence issues, anger management, and addictions. Arishna has a special interest in treating mood disorders particularly in the context of Borderline Personality Disorder and Complex PTSD.

locations.title: Brandon Srot
locations.description: Based in Sydney's inner City, Brandon is a psychotherapist and leadership development facilitator whose passion is developing human potential. Through a suite of services, Brandon works with you to achieve inner and outer connection so that you can enjoy the fullness of your life and arrive at your place of personal and professional excellence.

locations.title: Dean Harrison
locations.description: Life at times can be challenging, even overwhelming. It is important at these times that we connect with others for support. Sometimes though, our friends and family are not able to provide the level of support we need or do not have the skills to help us. At these times, it is good to seek professional help from a psychologist trained to assist people resolve difficulties.

locations.title: Michael Morris Cohn
locations.description: Therapy can be described as a relationship between two people, where one person has fewer problems than the other, and that person, one hopes, is the therapist. I am an ACT based, Buddhist therapist who has tried to develop an eclectic mix of mindfulness-based CBT.

locations.title: Stacey McCraw
locations.description: Stacey is a psychologist with experience in assisting adults and young people adjust to stressful life events such as grief, relationship distress, and workplace or financial difficulty; as well as treat longstanding symptoms of anxiety or low mood.
